<item>
            <title>[MNG-2302] SCM path calculations don&apos;t work when parent and grandparent are in sibling directories</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-2302</link>
                <project id="12316922" key="MNG">Maven (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have the following directory structure:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-top&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt; +-grandparent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt; +-parent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt; +-child&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where modules are specified in grandparent and parent, respectively, as:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;module&amp;gt;../parent&amp;lt;/module&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;module&amp;gt;../child&amp;lt;/module&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I put these into Continuum, and it tries to use the SCM info provided in the grandparent, it winds up thinking the child directory is a subdirectory of the parent directory.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
